G–00002 — DOCSYS DOCUMENT CREATION GOVERNANCE

Template and Governance for All DOCSYS Document Classes

Based on the “DOCSYS Index Hierarchy Overview” Conversation

1. Purpose

This Page defines the governance, structure, and required process for creating any DOCSYS document. It serves as the root template for all P‐Class, W‐Class, R‐Class, A‐Class, D‐Class, CR‐Class, and X‐Class documents. It incorporates the principles established in the DOCSYS Index Hierarchy Overview conversation and formalizes them into a unified, constitutional governance standard.

2. Scope

This governance applies to:

All DOCSYS document classes

All template definitions

All document creation workflows

All identity assignments (DOC ID, AUID)

All revisions, publications, and archival events

It does not apply to L‐Class, which belongs to the Record Architecture and is governed separately.

3. Identity Architecture Requirements

DOCSYS documents must comply with the UNISYS Identity Architecture:

3.1 DOC ID (Template Identity)

Assigned when the document type is defined

Format: <ClassPrefix>-00000 for templates

Format: <ClassPrefix>-00001+ for documents

Zero padded, 5 digit serial

Namespace agnostic

Immutable

3.2 AUID (Artifact Identity)

Assigned when a document is instantiated, executed, or published

Sequential, global, immutable

Tracks provenance and lifecycle

3.3 UDIS (Instance Identity)

Assigned when a physical/digital instance exists

Independent of DOC ID and AUID

4. Document Class Definitions

Each DOCSYS class has a specific purpose:

4.1 P‐Class — Procedures

Defines required steps, responsibilities, and controls.

4.2 W‐Class — Workflows

Defines operational sequences, transitions, and state logic.

4.3 R‐Class — Reviews

Defines evaluation, readiness, compliance, or audit checks. Verifications are included as part of this class, representing evaluation and compliance activities.

4.4 A‐Class — Analysis

Defines structured analytical documents, including evaluations interpreting aggregated data.

4.5 D‐Class — Datasets

Defines structured data collections, including aggregated or raw data from queries.

4.6 CR‐Class — Change Requests

Defines requests to create, modify, or retire documents.

4.7 X‐Class — Crosswalks

Defines mappings between namespaces, systems, or classifications.

4.8 REP‐Class — Reports

Defines documents that aggregate, summarize, or present findings and status reports distinct from Reviews. Reports provide structured documentation of operational or analytical results.

5. Document Creation Workflow

All DOCSYS documents must follow this creation process:

5.1 Initiation

Triggered by operational need, governance requirement, or CR-Class request.

Document class is selected.

Once a document class is assigned, find the highest number with the corresponding prefix and assign the new document with that number incremented by 1.

DOC ID is assigned.

5.2 Drafting

Document is authored using the class template.

Required sections must be included.

Cross-references must be validated.

5.3 Review

Peer or system review is performed.

Compliance with identity architecture is verified.

5.4 Publication

AUID is assigned.

Document is added to the DOCSYS index.

Document becomes authoritative.

5.5 Revision

Revisions require a CR-Class request.

New AUID is assigned for each revision.

5.6 Archival

Retired documents are archived with their AUID.

DOC ID remains permanently assigned.

6. Required Document Structure

All DOCSYS documents must include:

Title

DOC ID

AUID (once created)

Purpose

Scope

Definitions (if applicable)

Governance or procedural content

Cross-references

Revision history

