8. Compliance Requirements

All DOCSYS documents must:

Use the correct DOC ID

Assign AUIDs upon creation

Follow the class template

Maintain revision history

Reference crosswalks where applicable

Comply with UNISYS Identity Architecture

9. Summary

This Page establishes the governance, identity rules, and creation workflow for all DOCSYS documents. It is the authoritative template for document creation and ensures consistency, traceability, and architectural integrity across the entire system.

This Page is assigned the DOC ID P‐00000 and governs all subsequent DOCSYS document creation.

10. Notes on Evaluations and Data Aggregation

Evaluations interpreting aggregated data from queries or datasets belong to the A-Class (Analysis).

Aggregated or raw data collections resulting from queries belong to the D-Class (Datasets).

Reports (REP-Class) provide structured documentation of findings and status, distinct from Reviews (R-Class).

